      <body>
         <div type="entry">
                <head>Aitalaha</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Aitalaha</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/35</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">26</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="13"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/326</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">
                        <abbr>Bp.</abbr> of <placeName type="diocese" subtype="general">Edessa</placeName> (324/5-345/6).<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(first half of 4th <abbr>cent.</abbr>)</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>
                        <abbr>Bp.</abbr> of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Edessa">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>
                        </ref> (324/5–345/6). A short work in Armenian is transmitted
                        under his name and the editor described it as being addressed ‘to the
                        Christians in the region of Persia, on Faith’. Although it has been claimed
                        (by de Durand) that the original was Greek (and the work is listed in <hi rend="italic">
                            <abbr>CPG</abbr>
                        </hi> 3340), it is almost certainly a translation from
                        Syriac. The theological phraseology makes it very unlikely that the work
                        really belongs to the first half of the 4th <abbr>cent.</abbr> (thus Bruns), and it would
                        best fit sometime between 410 and 428 (thus Bundy).</p>
                </div>
                <div type="bibl">
                    <listBibl>
                        <listBibl>
                            <head>Primary Sources</head>
                            <bibl>P. Bruns, in <title rend="italic">
                                    <abbr>OC</abbr>
                                </title> 77 (1993), 120–36.
                                (<abbr>GT</abbr>)</bibl>
                            <bibl>J. Thorossian (Tʿorosean), <title rend="italic">Aithallae Episcopi
                                    Edesseni Epistula ad Christianos in Persarum regione de
                                    Fide</title> (1942). (Armenian with <abbr>LT</abbr>)</bibl>
                        </listBibl>
                        <listBibl>
                            <head>Secondary Sources</head>
                            <bibl>P. Bruns, ‘Aitallahas Brief über den Glauben. Ein bedeutendes
                                Dokument frühsyrischer Theologie’, <title rend="italic">
                                    <abbr>OC</abbr>
                                </title> 76
                                (1992), 46–73.</bibl>
                            <bibl>D. Bundy, ‘The Letter of Aithallah (<abbr>CPG</abbr> 3340): theology, purpose
                                and date’, in <abbr>
                                    <title rend="italic">SymSyr</title> III</abbr>,
                                135–42.</bibl>
                            <bibl>
                        <choice>
                           <reg>D. Bundy</reg>
                           <orig>idem</orig>
                        </choice>, ‘The Creed of Aithallah’, <title rend="italic">
                                    <abbr>ETL</abbr>
                                </title> 63
                                (1987), 157–63.</bibl>
                            <bibl>M. G.  de Durand, ‘Un document sur le Concile de Nicée?’<choice>
                                    <sic>,</sic>
                                    <corr/>
                                </choice> 
                        <title rend="italic">
                                    <abbr>RSPR </abbr>
                                </title>50 (1966), 615–27.</bibl>
                            <bibl>G. Winkler, ‘Über die Entwicklungsgeschichte des armenischen
                                Symbolums’ (<abbr>OCA</abbr> 262; 2000), 140–8.</bibl>
                        </listBibl>
                    </listBibl>
                </div>
